value.value: A shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is an elongation of the floral axis that supports the carpel (PO:0009030).

definition.value: A gynophore is only present when there is an elongation of the axis between the androecium and gynoecium. Found in peanut.

value.value: A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is a ridge on a seed (PO:0009010) that develops from a raphe (PO:0020027).
A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is attached to a seed (PO:0009010) and is the remnants of a funicle (PO:0020006).
A remnant of the ovular chalaza that is part of the seed.
A plant anatomical space that is enclosed by and forms an opening in a seed coat at the apex of a seed and is the remnant of a micropyle.
An outgrowth of the seed funicle, that forms a bridge between the seed micropyle and other tissues. It is also a remnant form of the obturator found in the ovular funicle.
A vascular leaf that is part of a plant embryo and is one of the first few leaves to develop from the embryonic shoot apical meristem.

definition.value: This term is used to described not yet fully-developed leaves that are part of an embryo.

value.value: A vascular leaf that is distinct from adult leaves, being characterized by particular anatomical traits namely, wax and trichome distribution, presence or absence of epidermal cell types, cell wall shape and biochemistry.

definition.value: Many species have juvenile leaves at the base of the stem, adult leaves at the apex, and transition leaves in between. In maize, juvenile leaves are at the tip of the stalk (stem), which differentiates first, with adult leaves at the base, while other grasses may have other arrangements. The first juvenile leaves in Poaceae are the embryonic leaves found in the grass kernel (caryopsis).

value.value: A vascular leaf characterized by particular anatomical traits namely, wax and trichome distribution, presence or absence of epidermal cell types, cell wall shape and biochemistry.

definition.value: Many species have juvenile leaves at the base of the stem, adult leaves at the apex, and transition leaves in between. In maize, juvenile leaves are at the tip of the stalk (stem), which differentiates first, with adult leaves at the base, while other grasses may have other arrangements. In some plants the juvenile leaves may go on to establish as adult leaves.

value.value: A shoot system (PO:0009006) that develops from an embryo shoot apical meristem (PO:0006362).

A reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) that develops from an inflorescence (PO:0009049) and has as parts each infructescence axis (PO:0025242) and all of the fruits (PO:0009001) borne by those axes.
A shoot-borne shoot system (PO:0004545) that develops from an axillary bud (PO:0004709).
A lateral meristem (PO:0020145) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).

An intercalary meristem (PO:0006073) that is part of a leaf (PO:0006346) and is intercalated between two portions of non-meristematic tissue between a leaf apex (PO:0020137) and a leaf base (PO:0020040).

definition.value: Results in an increase in length of a leaf, as part of primary growth. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf. The leaf intercalary meristem does not include a leaf plate meristem (PO:0025429) .

value.value: An intercalary meristem (PO:0006073) that is part of a stem internode (PO:0020142) and is intercalated between two portions of non-meristematic tissue.

definition.value: Results in an increase in length of a stem internode, as part of primary growth.

value.value: An ear spikelet (PO:0006320) which is the ultimate, pedicellate, higher order inflorescence axis (PO:0009081) of the maize ear inflorescence (PO:0020136).

definition.value: Develops from the ear spikelet pair meristem (PO:0006360).

value.value: An ear spikelet (PO:0006320) which is the ultimate, sessile, higher order inflorescence axis (PO:0009081) of the maize ear inflorescence (PO:0020136).

definition.value: Develops from the ear spikelet pair meristem (PO:0006360).

label.value: upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear

value.value: An ear floret that is the upper of the two florets of a pedicellate spikelet rachilla of an ear inflorescence.

definition.value: The upper floret on the ear usually develops into a functional one.

label.value: lower floret of sessile spikelet of ear

value.value: An ear floret that is the lower of the two florets on a sessile spikelet of an ear inflorescence.

definition.value: This floret does not usually develop into a functional one.

label.value: upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear

value.value: An ear floret that is one of the two florets placed above the lower floret on a sessile spikelet rachilla of an ear inflorescence.

definition.value: This floret usually develops into a functional one.

label.value: lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear

value.value: An ear floret that is the lower of the two florets of a pedicellate spikelet rachilla of an ear inflorescence.

definition.value: The lower floret on the ear does not usually develop into a functional one.

value.value: A small, pistillate flower (PO:0025599) that is part of a ear spikelet (PO:0006320).

definition.value: The ear floret (PO:0006354) initiates both carpels (PO:0009030) and stamens (PO:0009029), but all stamens abort during development. Found in Zea spp.

value.value: The meristem present on short tassel branch that produces two spikelet meristems, each of which produces two floral meristems in a maize tassel.

An ear inflorescence axillary meristem (PO:0009110) that produces two ear spikelet meristems (PO:0006378), each of which produces two flower meristems (PO:0000229) in an ear inflorescence (PO:0020136).
A vegetative shoot apical meristem at the apex of the embryonic axis.
